text.tspan: Self-reported life satisfaction vs. GDP per capita, 2011 to 2023
Self-reported life satisfaction is measured on a scale ranging from 0-10, where 10 is the highest possible life
satisfaction. GDP per capita is adjusted for inflation and differences in living costs between countries.
Data source: World Happiness Report (2012-2024); Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank (2025)

Note: GDP per capita is expressed in
international-$
at 2021 prices.
